parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Passenger Airbag Sensor Mat and Seat Cushion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective passenger airbag sensor mat and seat cushion can cause the airbag to not deploy during a crash if a front passenger is undetected, increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the passenger airbag light always indicates that no one is sitting in the passenger seat even when it is occupied
the front seat passenger occupancy sensor mat is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause a complete loss of steering, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in death or injury.
symptoms: The steering column detaches from the steering rack
making it impossible to steer the vehicle
and may occur without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spongy or excessive brake pedal travel can lead to reduced braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and may have excessive travel
making it difficult to stop the vehicle
and in some cases
causing unintended acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front stabilizer bar can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in death or injury.
symptoms: The front stabilizer bar breaks in half
which can occur while the vehicle is in motion
and may cause loss of control or instability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel pump leaks can cause sluggish engine performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine stalling or fires.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may experience sluggish performance
and in some cases
may stall or have difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering column knock and vibration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in death or injury.
symptoms: A knocking or vibration noise occurs when turning the vehicle at low speeds
which can be felt through the steering wheel and driver's seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Rear Cabin Modules
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water moisture entering the rear cabin can cause the rear camera and vehicle proximity sensors to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear camera and vehicle proximity sensors are not working
water moisture accumulation in the rear cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt sensor can trigger the airbag light, indicating a potential safety risk, and may lead to unnecessary repairs or even render the vehicle unsafe to drive.
symptoms: Airbag light comes on
seat belt sensor defective
potential safety risk.
